yone could simply track the spawn of named mobs, detect stats of mob, track every mob location in a zone and know other &quot;hidden&quot; info that is normally not available to players then this will be VERY unfair to those who chose rather not to use such 3rd party software. This is also considered cheating. You may try to argue, why don't everyone use ShowEQ then? The game is calibrated to test the player's skill, luck, and resourcefulness. That's how some people can advance further in game than others. If that challenge is taken away from the players then Everquest will degenerate into a no-skill game with pretty graphics. All the tactics and strategy to play successfully will be no longer be required. Let's not even mention the catastrophic devastation that will happen to the game economy. If everyone who uses showEQ will be able to track and farm all the mobs that drops equipment the second they pop then there will be a huge surplus of equipment introduced into the market. Remember, every piece of equipment dropped by the mob stays in the server economy virtually forever (unless someone loss their corpse or something). Verant would be forced to compensate by reducing the drops even further (and it's perfectly within their power too). It maybe fun to farm all the goodies you every wanted but in the end, you will only get bored with a good game and leave. Look what happened to UO, look what happened to Asheron's Call. They are both good games that is (nearly) destroyed by cheaters and 3rd party software.<br>
<br>
Some people may say &quot;Hey I'm doing this to screw Sony and/or Verant&quot;. But in reality, you're only screwing yourself and 1000s of other players who want to play a good game.<br>
<br>
Please think about it.<br>
